In [11]:
import re
lines = open('../annotation/hase_1.txt', 'r').readlines()
frames = []
states= []
for line in lines:
    x = re.split(r'\t+', line)[1:]
    frames.append(round(float(x[-2])*5))
    states.append(int(x[-1][0]))

In [13]:
df_head.loc[df_head.eval('0 <= frame <= 191'), 'state'] = 1

for i in range(1, len(frames)):
    condition = str(frames[i-1]) + '<= frame <=' + str(frames[i])
    df_head.loc[df_head.eval(condition), 'state'] = states[i]

In [26]:
def plot_clusters(X,R):
    # sort columns by total responsibility
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
    plt.figure()
    Rsum = np.sum(R,axis=0)
    R = R[:,np.argsort(Rsum)]
    ax.scatter(X[:, 0], X[:, 1], color=R, s=6)
    ax.set_xlabel('Principal Component 1', size=14)
    ax.set_ylabel('Principal Component 2', size=14)
    ax.set_title('Soft clustering by GMM', size=16)
    plt.show()
